
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specified location in a node hierarchy. It targets the children of the [signal] node under the [exe] node and adds three new nodes: [to], [from], and [channel], each with expressions pointing to their respective nodes. The [add] slot facilitates dynamic modification of node structures by inserting new nodes into specified locations.
add:x:@.exe/*/signal
   .
      to:x:@.from
      from:x:@.to
      channel:x:@.channel
